@page "/change-log"
@layout PublicLayout

<PageTitle>What's New — Chronicis</PageTitle>

<div class="static-page">
    <div class="static-page-content changelog-page">
        <h1>What's New</h1>
        <p class="changelog-subtitle">See what we've been working on</p>

        @* 3.0 — Maps *@
        <section class="changelog-section">
            <div class="changelog-version">
                <span class="version-badge">3.0</span>
                <span class="version-date">March 2026</span>
            </div>
            <h2>World Maps</h2>
            <p class="changelog-summary">
                Maps are now first-class in Chronicis. Create maps with basemap image uploads,
                manage them from a dedicated Maps Detail page, and open each map in its own
                route with consistent breadcrumbs and tree navigation state.
            </p>
            <ul class="changelog-features">
                <li>
                    <span class="feature-icon">🗺️</span>
                    <div>
                        <strong>World Maps with Basemap Images</strong> — Maps now live under a
                        dedicated sidebar section and open map-specific pages. Create maps with a
                        name plus image upload (browse or drag/drop), rename maps from the map-page
                        header, and permanently delete maps from Maps Detail using typed-name
                        confirmation.
                    </div>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <span class="feature-icon">🧭</span>
                    <div>
                        <strong>Maps Navigation and Page Flow</strong> — The Maps tree node now
                        opens Maps Detail (instead of creating an uncategorized article), map pages
                        include breadcrumbs, and the active map stays selected in the nav tree.
                    </div>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        @* 2.12 — Collaborative Sessions & Onboarding *@
        <section class="changelog-section">
            <div class="changelog-version">
                <span class="version-badge">2.12</span>
                <span class="version-date">February 2026</span>
            </div>
            <h2>Collaborative Sessions, Tutorial World &amp; DM Planning</h2>
            <p class="changelog-summary">
                Every player can now contribute their own session notes, a pre-built tutorial
                world helps you get started immediately, a contextual help sidebar guides you
                on every page, and DMs get dedicated private planning notes across the app.
            </p>
            <ul class="changelog-features">
                <li>
                    <span class="feature-icon">📝</span>
                    <div>
                        <strong>Multi-Author Session Notes</strong> — Each player can now write
                        their own session note. When a session is created a default note is added
                        for the creator; any other party member can add their own with the
                        "Add Session Note" button. The AI summary reads <em>all</em> notes to
                        produce a complete picture of the session.
                    </div>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <span class="feature-icon">🌍</span>
                    <div>
                        <strong>Tutorial World</strong> — New accounts start with a fully
                        populated example world to explore. It's a real, playable campaign
                        setting — not just placeholder text — so you can see exactly how
                        Chronicis works before building your own.
                    </div>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <span class="feature-icon">🧭</span>
                    <div>
                        <strong>Contextual Help Sidebar</strong> — A new help panel appears on
                        every page and knows where you are. Open it any time for tips specific
                        to World pages, Campaign pages, Sessions, Characters, and more. When
                        you're exploring the tutorial world it stays open automatically so
                        guidance is always visible.
                    </div>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <span class="feature-icon">🔒</span>
                    <div>
                        <strong>Private Planning Notes for GMs</strong> — World, Campaign, Arc,
                        and Session detail pages now each have a Private Notes tab, visible only
                        to the GM. Jot down plot hooks, upcoming encounter ideas, or secret lore
                        without any risk of players seeing it. GMs can also mark any Session Note
                        as private for more structured planning.
                    </div>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        @* February 2026 *@
        <section class="changelog-section">
            <div class="changelog-version">
                <span class="version-badge">2.11</span>
                <span class="version-date">February 2026</span>
            </div>
            <h2>Inline Article Images</h2>
            <p class="changelog-summary">
                Drop, paste, or pick images directly into your session notes and wiki articles. 
                Images upload to the cloud and display inline — no separate attachment step needed.
            </p>
            <ul class="changelog-features">
                <li>
                    <span class="feature-icon">🖼️</span>
                    <div>
                        <strong>Drag &amp; Drop</strong> — Drop an image file anywhere in the editor 
                        to upload and insert it inline
                    </div>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <span class="feature-icon">📋</span>
                    <div>
                        <strong>Paste from Clipboard</strong> — Copy an image and paste it directly 
                        into your notes with <code>Ctrl+V</code>
                    </div>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <span class="feature-icon">🔘</span>
                    <div>
                        <strong>Toolbar Button</strong> — Use the image button above the editor to 
                        pick a file from your device
                    </div>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <span class="feature-icon">🔒</span>
                    <div>
                        <strong>Secure Storage</strong> — Images are stored in Azure Blob Storage 
                        with authenticated access and time-limited download URLs
                    </div>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <span class="feature-icon">🧹</span>
                    <div>
                        <strong>Automatic Cleanup</strong> — Deleting an article removes its 
                        associated images from storage automatically
                    </div>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="changelog-section">
            <div class="changelog-version">
                <span class="version-badge">2.10</span>
                <span class="version-date">February 2026</span>
            </div>
            <h2>Quest Tracking</h2>
            <p class="changelog-summary">
                Keep your party's objectives organized and track progress in real-time. The new quest 
                system integrates directly into your session workflow with a dedicated quest journal.
            </p>
            <ul class="changelog-features">
                <li>
                    <span class="feature-icon">🎯</span>
                    <div>
                        <strong>Quest Management</strong> — Create and track quests for each story arc 
                        with status tracking (Active, Completed, Failed)
                    </div>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <span class="feature-icon">⌨️</span>
                    <div>
                        <strong>Quick Access</strong> — Press <code>Ctrl+Q</code> while viewing a session 
                        to open the quest drawer and add updates instantly
                    </div>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <span class="feature-icon">📔</span>
                    <div>
                        <strong>Quest Journal</strong> — Record progress with markdown-powered updates 
                        that automatically link to the current session
                    </div>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <span class="feature-icon">🔗</span>
                    <div>
                        <strong>Wiki Links in Updates</strong> — Reference characters, locations, and 
                        items using <code>[[article]]</code> syntax right in your quest updates
                    </div>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <span class="feature-icon">📚</span>
                    <div>
                        <strong>SRD Integration</strong> — Link to spells, monsters, and magic items 
                        from the D&D SRD using <code>[[srd/resource]]</code> in quest descriptions
                    </div>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <span class="feature-icon">⏱️</span>
                    <div>
                        <strong>Recent Updates Timeline</strong> — See the last 10 quest journal entries 
                        at a glance to track recent progress
                    </div>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <span class="feature-icon">🎨</span>
                    <div>
                        <strong>Status Badges</strong> — Color-coded quest status (green for active, 
                        blue for completed, red for failed) makes it easy to see what's in progress
                    </div>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        @* January 2026 *@
        <section class="changelog-section">
            <div class="changelog-version">
                <span class="version-badge">2.7</span>
                <span class="version-date">January 2026</span>
            </div>
            <h2>External Knowledge Links</h2>
            <p class="changelog-summary">
                Bring your reference material directly into your notes. Link to external sources like
                the D&D 5e SRD using the same wiki-style workflow, with rich in-app previews.
            </p>
            <ul class="changelog-features">
                <li>
                    <span class="feature-icon">📚</span>
                    <div>
                        <strong>SRD Autocomplete</strong> — Type <code>[[srd/</code> in any article to search
                        spells, monsters, and other SRD content as you write
                    </div>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <span class="feature-icon">🔗</span>
                    <div>
                        <strong>External Link Chips</strong> — External references appear as visually
                        distinct link chips so you can easily tell them apart from your own articles
                    </div>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <span class="feature-icon">👁️</span>
                    <div>
                        <strong>In-App Previews</strong> — Click an external link to open a preview drawer
                        showing the full reference content without leaving Chronicis
                    </div>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <span class="feature-icon">🧩</span>
                    <div>
                        <strong>Extensible by Design</strong> — External sources are provider-based,
                        making it easy to add new reference libraries in the future
                    </div>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <span class="feature-icon">📊</span>
                    <div>
                        <strong>Structured Rendering</strong> — External resources display with
                        category-aware layouts, including D&amp;D-style stat blocks for bestiary
                        entries with compact ability score tables
                    </div>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </section>
        <section class="changelog-section">
            <div class="changelog-version">
